  "original_title": "Indictments filed against Johnston in Sathosa Case",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Indictments filed against Johnston in Sathosa Case",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "COLOMBO (News 1st); Indictments were filed against Former Minister Johnston Fernando, and two others in the case for causing losses to the state by deploying Sathosa workers for political activities in 2012.",
        "Indictments were filed against Former Minister Johnston Fernando, Former Sathosa Chairman Eraj Fernando, and Former Sathosa Director Raj Mohideen Mohammad Sakeer.",
        "Colombo High Court Judge Aditya Patabandige ordered for each suspect to be released on two personal bails, each amounting to Rs. 5 Million.",
        "The case is scheduled to be taken up again on the 21st of October.",
        "Tokyo will coordinate with other Sri Lanka creditors on debt"
      ],
